The Berlin2CD NFC shares the Marvell NFCv2 register layout but uses the
explicit command patterns for READID and RESET. Its production data path
also requires the pBridge descriptor engine, explicit BCH strength
programming and the vendor data randomizer. Add enough support to identify
the flash non-destructively while deliberately refusing to register an MTD
device.

This gives hardware bring-up a safe READID/parameter-page milestone without
making incomplete page reads or erase/program operations available to
userspace.

